Based on the relevant past event from June 2025, the solution provided was to use the hotkeys.js library to override the default browser behavior for the specified key combinations. Specifically, the code snippet used was:

```javascript
hotkeys('ctrl+s, ctrl+n, ctrl+t, ctrl+u', function(event, handler) {
    event.preventDefault();
    console.log('You pressed:', handler.key);
});
```

This code listens for the specified key combinations (`CTRL+S`, `CTRL+N`, `CTRL+T`, `CTRL+U`) and prevents their default actions, logging which key was pressed.
